{"pageProps":{"course":{"name":"Italian 1","department":"Foreign Language","description":"Italian 1 is a beginning language course that enables students to communicate, read, and write in Italian. Students practice Italian in simulated, realistic situations. As they learn the language structure, they perform the communicative functions of socializing, exchanging information, counting, expressing feelings and emotions, and persuading. Learners engage in critical thinking through analysis and comparisons of culture and language, and explore the target language beyond the classroom in real-world interactions within their own community. Students compare their culture to the Italian culture. They watch Italian films, create basic Italian dishes, sing Italian songs, participate in Italian heritage festivals, and report on important Italian historical figures.","AtoG":"E-Language other than English","length":"Yearlong","prerequisites":[],"classes":[{"name":"Italian 1","block":"4","semester":"Fall2014","teacher":{"name":"Chiara Pelagatti"}},{"name":"Italian 1","block":"6","semester":"Fall2014","teacher":{"name":"Chiara Pelagatti"}},{"name":"Italian 1","block":"4","semester":"Spring2015","teacher":{"name":"Chiara Pelagatti"}},{"name":"Italian 1","block":"6","semester":"Spring2015","teacher":{"name":"Chiara Pelagatti"}},{"name":"Italian 1","block":"5","semester":"Fall2015","teacher":{"name":"Undetermined"}},{"name":"Italian 1","block":"6","semester":"Fall2015","teacher":{"name":"Undetermined"}},{"name":"Italian 1","block":"5","semester":"Spring2016","teacher":{"name":"Maria Luisa DeSeta"}},{"name":"Italian 1","block":"6","semester":"Spring2016","teacher":{"name":"Maria Luisa DeSeta"}},{"name":"Italian 1","block":"5","semester":"Fall2016","teacher":{"name":"Maria Luisa DeSeta"}},{"name":"Italian 1","block":"6","semester":"Fall2016","teacher":{"name":"Maria Luisa DeSeta"}},{"name":"Italian 1","block":"5","semester":"Spring2017","teacher":{"name":"Maria Luisa DeSeta"}},{"name":"